=== Hardware wiring preflight

The streaming SPI tests prove protocol behaviour only after the
master can already see the slave. They do not, by themselves, prove
that `spi.pcf` matches the actual harness wiring. The preflight uses
two existing fixtures to make that explicit:

  - a walking-pin FPGA bitstream starts with the QSPI pins
    high-impedance so the MP135 boots without any external driver;
  - the MP135 firmware's `G` command disables QUADSPI and switches
    `CLK/NCS/IO0/IO1/IO2/IO3` to GPIO inputs;
  - the same FPGA bitstream then drives `00, 01, 02, 04, 08, 10, 20`
    on those six pins while the MP135 reads them back.

This keeps the preflight useful when the iCEstick UART channel is not
available: the observed evidence is the MP135 UART log alone, and every
programmed FPGA drive pattern is checked from the MPU side.

