=== Hardware test plan

Two phases, each one fenced block per `(mode, prescaler)` so a
failure pins down exactly which (lane-count, SCLK) pair broke.
Every block reflashes the MP135 firmware from `flash.tsv`,
opens the MP135 console, sets the prescaler, and issues the raw bench
command. The 1-lane phase reuses the `spi_1lane.bin` image already
loaded by the 1-lane preflight block, avoiding repeated FPGA
reprogramming while the iCEstick USB side is recovering. The success
sentinel is the final summary field `, firsterr=-1`, after the whole
megabyte has been validated against the incrementing pattern. Bare
`firsterr` is not unique when BENCHDBG emits intermediate diagnostics.

The prescaler sweep covers 203 (~1.63 MHz wire), 63 (~5.19 MHz),
15 (~20.75 MHz), 5 (~55.3 MHz), 4 (~66.4 MHz), 3 (~83 MHz),
2 (~110.7 MHz), and 1 (~166 MHz);
timeouts shrink with prescaler since the bench finishes faster
at higher SCLK.

